# Phase 1 Todo App - Intermediate and Advanced Features

A CLI-based Python todo application supporting task management with priorities, categories, search, filtering, sorting, due dates, and recurring tasks.

## Features

### Basic Features (Existing)
- âœ… Create tasks
- âœ… Delete tasks
- âœ… Update tasks
- âœ… View tasks
- âœ… Mark complete/incomplete

### Intermediate Features (Phase 1)
- ğŸ¯ **Priorities**: Assign priority levels (high, medium, low) to tasks
- ğŸ·ï¸ **Categories**: Organize tasks by category/tags
- ğŸ” **Search**: Find tasks by keyword
- ğŸ” **Filtering**: Filter tasks by status, priority, category (combinable)
- â†•ï¸ **Sorting**: Sort by priority, due date, title

### Advanced Features (Phase 1)
- ğŸ“… **Due Dates**: Assign optional due dates with validation and overdue detection
- ğŸ”„ **Recurring Tasks**: Create daily, weekly, or monthly recurring tasks with auto-generation

## Installation

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.13+
- pip or uv package manager

### Setup

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone <repo-url>
cd todo-app

# Install dependencies
pip install -e ".[dev]"
# or with uv
uv sync
```

## Usage

### Basic Commands

```bash
# Add a task with priority and category
python -m src.cli add "Buy groceries" --priority HIGH --category personal

# List all tasks
python -m src.cli list

# Filter tasks
python -m src.cli list --filter-priority HIGH --filter-category work

# Search tasks
python -m src.cli list --search "grocery"

# Sort tasks
python -m src.cli list --sort-by DUE_DATE --sort-order ASC

# Update a task
python -m src.cli update task-001 --priority MEDIUM --category work

# Mark task complete (triggers recurrence generation if recurring)
python -m src.cli complete task-001

# Delete task
python -m src.cli delete task-001
```

### Advanced Examples

```bash
# Create recurring task
python -m src.cli add "Daily standup" --recurrence DAILY --category work

# Filter with multiple criteria (AND logic)
python -m src.cli list \
  --filter-status INCOMPLETE \
  --filter-priority HIGH \
  --filter-category work \
  --sort-by DUE_DATE

# Create task with due date
python -m src.cli add "Pay bills" --due-date 2025-12-31 --priority HIGH
```

